body:
@keith-turner If you can, I'd love your feedback on this. In particular, I think it raises an interesting question about what the default value for these compaction properties should be, in order to not break expectations for people who have overridden the default value for `tserver.compaction.major.concurrent.max`.

Specifically, I was thinking maybe we'd want to use `tserver.compaction.major.concurrent.max` value, if different from the default (assuming `tserver.compaction.major.service.default.planner.opts.executors` is still set to the default), and interpret it similarly to my single "any" pool with the max threads equal to whatever the older property was set to, and no size limits (perhaps with a warning about the property being deprecated, and how it is being interpreted).

What do you think?
